Name: centronuclear myopathy 6 with fiber-type disproportion
Definition: A congenital fiber-type disproportion characterized by onset in infancy or early childhood of slowly progressive centronuclear myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in ZAK on 2q31.1.

Name: X-linked congenital myopathy with fiber-type disproportion
Definition: A congenital fiber-type disproportion characterized by bilateral ptosis
